  "prompt": "Personal Productivity: Is there a service that allows bookmarking of quotes?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several services and apps designed for bookmarking quotes:\n\n1. Digital Quote Managers:\n- Goodreads (quotes from books)\n- Readwise\n- Liner\n- Pocket\n- Evernote\n\n2. Quote-Specific Services:\n- Quotely\n- QuoteBack\n- Quoty\n- Quote Unquote\n\n3. Browser Extensions:\n- Hypothesis\n- Diigo\n- Raindrop.io\n\n4. Note-Taking Apps with Quote Features:\n- Notion\n- Roam Research\n- Obsidian\n- OneNote\n\n5. Mobile Apps:\n- Quote Keeper\n- QuoteLife\n- Quote Collector\n\nSome features to look for:\n- Ability to save quotes\n- Tagging/categorization\n- Search functionality\n- Sync across devices\n- Optional citation/source tracking\n\nRecommendation: Try a few and see which workflow suits you best. Many offer free versions or trials.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these options?",
